{"title":"Reaper","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Reaper","type":"markdown","data":"| )   Reaper   *(No tile)*              |                                                                       |\n| ------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Base item                             | [halberd](/wiki/Halberd \"Halberd\")                                    |\n|                                       |                                                                       |\n| Damage vs. small                      | 1d8 **+20**                                                           |\n| Damage vs. large                      | 1d12 **+20**                                                          |\n| To-hit bonus                          | **+5**                                                                |\n| Bonus versus                          | *(any)*                                                               |\n|                                       |                                                                       |\n| Weapon skill                          | [polearms](/wiki/Polearms \"Polearms\")                                 |\n| Size                                  | two-handed                                                            |\n| Affiliation                           | - [lawful](/wiki/Lawful \"Lawful\")\n- [(Yeoman)](/wiki/Yeoman \"Yeoman\") |\n|                                       |                                                                       |\n| When carried                          | *(none)*                                                              |\n| When wielded                          | *(none)*                                                              |\n| When [invoked](/wiki/Invoke \"Invoke\") | *(none)*                                                              |\n|                                       |                                                                       |\n| Base price                            | 1000 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\")                                    |\n| Weight                                | [150](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                                          |\n| Material                              | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\")                                             |\n\n**Reaper** is a [lawful](/wiki/Lawful \"Lawful\") [artifact](/wiki/Artifact \"Artifact\") [halberd](/wiki/Halberd \"Halberd\") in [SLASH'EM](/wiki/SLASH%27EM \"SLASH'EM\"). It has +5 to hit and +20 to damage when [pounding](/wiki/Pounding \"Pounding\"). It is the guaranteed second sacrifice gift for [yeomen](/wiki/Yeoman \"Yeoman\").\n\n## Strategy\n\nThis weapon is tied with the [Bat from Hell](/wiki/Bat_from_Hell \"Bat from Hell\") for the highest damage bonus in the game that works against any monster, and has a higher base damage. Unfortunately, it is somewhat less useful for most roles, since its damage bonus only applies when pounding or when attacking from a mount, and it requires both hands thus preventing two weapon combat. Its utility depends on your play style: if you are making thorough use of [riding](/wiki/Riding \"Riding\") and polearms, it is possibly the best artifact weapon in the game. If instead you are simply playing as a straightforward fighter, it is better to use as a supplement to a more traditional melee weapon.\n\nNote that both [Mjollnir](/wiki/Mjollnir \"Mjollnir\") at +24 and [Disrupter](/wiki/Disrupter \"Disrupter\") at +30 have higher damage bonuses than Reaper, but Mjollnir's damage bonus doesn't apply to shock-resistant monsters, and Disrupter's only applies versus undead.\n\nA user has suggested improving this page or section as follows:\n\n*\"Update to reflect THEM/Hack'EM\"*\n\n[![This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH'EM. Click here for more information.](/images/3/38/Se7e7-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article may require revision for the next version of SLASH'EM. Click here for more information.\")\n\n[![This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Reaper - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Reaper\",\"wgTitle\":\"Reaper\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":158350,\"wgRevisionId\":158350,\"wgArticleId\":20175,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Todo\",\"Slashem-7E7 articles\",\"SLASH'EM\",\"Variant-343 articles\",\"SLASH'EM artifact weapons\",\"SlashTHEM artifact weapons\",\"Hack'EM artifact weapons\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Reaper\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":20175,\"wgRequestId\":\"0aa53b26ae96a925abdcc5a0\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiE